text: Anatetarte () or Anotetarte (Ἀνωτετάρτη) was a town of ancient Caria. It became a bishopric; no longer the seat of a residential bishop, it remains a titular see of the Roman Catholic Church.Catholic Hierarchy Its site is unlocated. ==References== Category:Populated places in ancient Caria Category:Catholic titular sees in Asia Category:Former populated places in Turkey Category:Roman towns and cities in Turkey Category:Lost ancient cities and towns
